# Flutter Clean Architecture


## File Placement

| Layer | Path |
|---|---|
| Entity | `features/{feature}/domain/entities/{name}_entity.dart` |
| Model | `features/{feature}/data/models/{name}_model.dart` |
| Params | `features/{feature}/domain/usecases/params/{Name}Params.dart` |
| Datasource | `features/{feature}/data/datasources/{feature}_remote_datasource.dart` |
| Repo interface | `features/{feature}/domain/repository/{feature}_repository.dart` |
| Repo impl | `features/{feature}/data/repository/{feature}_repository_impl.dart` |
| UseCase | `features/{feature}/domain/usecases/{action}_{feature}.dart` |
| Cubit | `features/{feature}/presentation/cubit/{feature}_cubit.dart` |
| State | `features/{feature}/presentation/cubit/{feature}_state.dart` |
| UI screen | `features/{feature}/presentation/screens/{feature}_screen.dart` |
| Feature widgets | `features/{feature}/presentation/widgets/{name}.dart` |
| DI | `features/{feature}/{feature}_injection.dart` |

## Code Style

- Null-safety everywhere. No `dynamic` unless unavoidable.
- `log` instead of `print`. Use `BlocObserver` for state debugging.
- Prefer `const` widgets. Prefer stateless widgets.
- Never `Widget _buildXxx()` methods. Split feature UI into **named widget
  classes** in `presentation/widgets/` (one file per widget or small group),
  not private classes in the screen file.
- Meaningful names for classes, methods, and variables.

## Core Priority

- Always check `lib/core/` before creating any helper, extension, widget, or utility.
- **Widgets:** Before adding inline UI or a new feature-local widget, scan
  `lib/core/widgets/` (and subfolders such as `shimmer/`). If a suitable
  widget exists there, import and use it first. Only build new UI when nothing
  in core fits.
- If it exists in core → use it. Never duplicate.
- Always use shared colors/theme tokens and any reusable resources from `lib/core/` before introducing new values or duplicate components.

## Constants

- All endpoints, keys, and route strings live in `lib/core/utils/constants.dart`.
- Never hardcode URLs or keys inside datasources, repositories, or UI.
- Add a new constant if missing; follow the existing naming style (`ApiConstants.xxx`, `ApiKeys.xxx`).

## Dependency Injection

- Service locator: `ServiceLocator.instance` (GetIt).
- Cubits → `registerFactory`. Services, use cases, repos → `registerLazySingleton`.
- Inject abstractions (interfaces), not concrete implementations.

## UI & Loading

- Loading state → shimmer from `lib/core/widgets/shimmer/`. No `CircularProgressIndicator` unless explicitly requested (then use `showLoading` from constants).
- Error state → `SelectableText.rich` in red. No SnackBars.
- Empty state → handled within the same screen.
- No business logic in UI. Cubit only.
- For localized strings in UI, always use translation extension syntax (`'key'.tr`) instead of direct `appLocalizations.text('key')` calls.
- **Typography:** Prefer `TextStyles` from `lib/core/utils/values/text_styles.dart`
  (Cairo via Google Fonts, `.sp` via ScreenUtil): use the numeric helpers
  (`bold32`, `medium16`, `semiBold18`, etc.). Prefer `.copyWith` for one-off
  tweaks (color, height, letterSpacing). Use `Theme.of(context).textTheme`
  only when no `TextStyles` helper fits (e.g. Material roles inside inputs).
  Add a new `boldNN` / `mediumNN` / `semiBoldNN` / `regularNN` static before
  inlining `TextStyle` in features.
- `RefreshIndicator` for pull-to-refresh.
- **Text fields:** Use `AppTextFormField` from
  `lib/core/widgets/app_text_form_field.dart` for form inputs instead of raw
  `TextFormField` / `TextField`. If a layout or behavior is missing, extend
  `AppTextFormField` in core first; do not duplicate field styling in features.
- `textCapitalization`, `keyboardType`, `textInputAction` on every text field
  (including `AppTextFormField`).
- `errorBuilder` on every `Image.network`.
- **Images:** Use `AppImage` from `lib/core/widgets/app_image.dart` in
  presentation UI — `AppImage.asset`, `AppImage.file`, or `AppImage.network`
  (set `isCached: true` when the URL should use disk cache). For **cached**
  remote images with shimmer + logo fallback, prefer
  `CachedNetworkImageWithFallback` from
  `lib/core/widgets/cached_network_image_with_fallback.dart`. Use paths/URLs
  from `ImageAssets` / constants in `lib/core/utils/values/img_manager.dart`
  (or existing asset URL constants). Do not use raw `Image.asset` /
  `Image.network` or import `package:cached_network_image` in feature code;
  keep those inside core only.
- Figma assets: icons must be downloaded/used as SVG; non-icon images must
  be downloaded/used as PNG or JPG.
- **ScreenUtil:** Presentation UI must scale layout with `flutter_screenutil`
  after `ScreenUtilInit` in `main.dart`. Import
  `package:flutter_screenutil/flutter_screenutil.dart`. Use `.w` for widths
  and horizontal insets, `.h` for heights and vertical insets, `.r` for
  border radii, icon sizes, and small square controls (unless already using
  `.sp` inside `TextStyles`). Avoid raw `double` literals for padding,
  `SizedBox`, `Container` width/height, and `BorderRadius.circular` in screens
  and feature widgets.

## Response Models

- List response → extend `BaseListResponse`.
- Single response → extend `BaseOneResponse`.
- List parse: `List<XModel>.from((json["data"]["key"] ?? []).map((x) => XModel.fromJson(x)))`
- Single parse: `json["data"] == null ? null : XModel.fromJson(json["data"])`

## Repository / UseCase Contracts

- Repository abstract methods return `Future<Either<Failure, Entity>>`.
- Repository impl converts model → entity and wraps exceptions as `Failure`.
- UseCase takes a `Params` object; returns `Either<Failure, Entity>`.
- Cubit has **one public method**. Emits: loading, success, failure. No model mapping.

## Navigation & Performance

- GoRouter for all navigation and deep linking.
- `ListView.builder` for lists. Remote images → `AppImage` or
  `CachedNetworkImageWithFallback` (see UI & Loading). Do not import
  `cached_network_image` in features; it stays in core.
